Good to know. Thanks! So I guess the moral is, if you have a big, expensive struct, make sure the expensive part is in a sub-structure you <i>know</i> is heap allocated, such as a Vec. E.g.:<p><pre><code>    struct Expensive {
        cheap_value: u32,
        expensive_value: Vec<u32>
    }
</code></pre>
Does that seem like a good maxim?

